Dental Fun Day (DBJ)
Grades: K, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5

Ever wonder how to keep your teeth sparkly white? Join the UF College of Dentistry and the American Association of Women Dentists for a fun filled day of activities to learn more about dental health. Taught by women dental students, this program will include fun activities on ways to brush and floss, keep your teeth sparkly white, basic tooth anatomy, proper nutrition to keep your teeth and body healthy, and how to maintain a beautiful smile. All registered girls receive a dental goodie bag with a toothbrush, floss, toothpaste and awesome Dental Health Fun Patch for your uniform. Fun patch included.

*This event is for 2016 registered Girl Scouts, and registered & approved adult volunteers.
* For safety and supervision reasons, troops and individuals are not permitted to bring non-Girl Scouts or siblings. 
*Girl/adult ratios must be followed and adults are expected to stay on the premises during the event. 

$3/girl, $1/adult
Contact: Brittany McCallister 904.389.3071
